set_vt_skew_config(25.10)                            set_vt_skew_config(25.10)

Name
       set_vt_skew_config  -  Allows  customization of the combinations of Vth
       classes to be analyzed

Syntax
       set_vt_skew_config

        [-help]

       [-analysis_mode {setup | hold | both}]

       [-clocks_only]

       [-correlated_vt_groups <<corr_group>>]

        [-exclude <<exclude>>]

        [-exclude_nominal]

       [-include_only <<include_only>>]

        [-unique_vt_mode {none | slow | fast | nominal}]

       Allows customization of the combinations of Vth classes to be analyzed.
       By default, the software will analyze all the possible combinations.

       This command is not cumulative as each invocation will  reset  any  op-
       tions  previously  set  by  its default value unless that option is re-
       specified.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -analysis_mode {setup | hold | both}
              Specifies the analysis mode for which the configuration is to be
              used.

       -clocks_only
              Allows the software to consider only launch  and  capture  clock
              VTs post CPPR point when enumerating Vth combinations.

              By  default,  the software will consider Vth classes on the data
              path as well.

       -correlated_vt_groups <corr_group>
              Specifies the groups for correlation.

              By default, all Vth groups are considered  uncorrelated.   If  a
              set  of  Vth groups is specified as correlated then they will be
              considered as one entity when determining  the  combinations  of
              Vth  groups.   All  the correlated VT's will use the same (fast,
              slow, nominal) derate factor.

       -exclude <exclude>
              Specifies the configurations to be excluded.

              When this parameter is specified,  the  software  excludes  some
              combinations of Vth classes from the full elaborated set of com-
              binations. The argument to this parameter is a Tcl list-of-lists
              as  described  for  -include_only.  The -exclude expression is a
              secondary filter which acts against the the current included set
              of enumerations - either all by default, or a subset  configured
              by -include_only.

       -exclude_nominal
              Determines whether to enumerate fast, slow, nominal combinations
              or just fast, slow.

       -include_only <include_only>
              Specifies the configurations to be included.

              You  can  specify  only the Vth combinations of interest. By de-
              fault, all the possible combinations are analyzed. The  argument
              to  this parameter is a Tcl list-of-lists structure, which asso-
              ciates a Vth group with the set of analyses to consider for that
              group.

              Note: The options for -include_only and -exclude parameters is a
              Tcl list-of-lists that provides a way to customize the Vth  enu-
              merations that are analyzed. The format is a Vth group name fol-
              lowed by an enum list of combinations of fast, slow, or nominal.
              If  a  Vth  group  is  missing from the specification a value of
              'all' will be assumed.

       -unique_vt_mode {none | slow | fast |nominal}
              Allows the software to consider  only  the  launch  and  capture
              clock VTs post CPPR point when enumerating Vth combinations.

              By  default,  the software will consider Vth classes on the data
              path as well. The unique Vt analysis  mode  is  applicable  only
              during the path-based analysis (PBA) step.

Examples
              * The  following  command defines the derate mode to use in both
                GBA and PBA when the path has unique VT:

                set_vt_skew_config -unique_vt_mode slow

                Setting a unique Vt mode is required for  the  GBA  unique  Vt
                flow.

